[{"location":"examples/makie/","page":"Makie.jl","title":"Makie.jl","text":"EditURL = \"makie.jl\"","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/makie/#Use-with-Makie.jl","page":"Makie.jl","title":"Use with Makie.jl","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"examples/makie/","page":"Makie.jl","title":"Makie.jl","text":"using CairoMakie\nusing PrideColorSchemes","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/makie/","page":"Makie.jl","title":"Makie.jl","text":"The palettes defined in PROUD_PALETTES can be used to set colors in Makie plots.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/makie/","page":"Makie.jl","title":"Makie.jl","text":"For example,","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/makie/","page":"Makie.jl","title":"Makie.jl","text":"x = 0:1e-2:2Ï€\nlines(x, cos, color = PROUD_PALETTES[:rainbow][1])\nlines!(x, sin, color = PROUD_PALETTES[:rainbow][2])\n\ncurrent_figure()","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/makie/","page":"Makie.jl","title":"Makie.jl","text":"They can also be used to set the palette for a whole plot. This can be simpler than setting colors one plot at a time.","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/makie/","page":"Makie.jl","title":"Makie.jl","text":"p = PROUD_PALETTES[:rainbow]\n\nfig = Figure()\nax = Axis(fig[1, 1], palette = (patchcolor = p,))\n\nfor (i, _) in enumerate(p)\n    y = @. sin(x) + i - 1\n    band!(ax, x, y, y .+ 1,)\nend\n\nfig","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/makie/","page":"Makie.jl","title":"Makie.jl","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"examples/makie/","page":"Makie.jl","title":"Makie.jl","text":"This page was generated using Literate.jl.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = PrideColorSchemes","category":"page"},{"location":"#PrideColorSchemes","page":"Home","title":"PrideColorSchemes","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for PrideColorSchemes.","category":"page"},{"location":"#API","page":"Home","title":"API","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [PrideColorSchemes]","category":"page"},{"location":"#PrideColorSchemes.PrideColorSchemes","page":"Home","title":"PrideColorSchemes.PrideColorSchemes","text":"Colour palettes\n\nFor flags composed of horizontal stripes, the colors in each array are ordered from bottom to top. This results in color bars with an intuitive order.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"module"},{"location":"#PrideColorSchemes.PROUD_PALETTES","page":"Home","title":"PrideColorSchemes.PROUD_PALETTES","text":"const PROUD_PALETTES::Dict{Symbol,Vector{Colors.RGB}}\n\nDict of RGB vectors.\n\nExamples\n\njulia> using PrideColorSchemes\n\njulia> PROUD_PALETTES[:pride]\n6-element Array{RGB,1} with eltype ColorTypes.RGB:\n RGB{N0f8}(0.459,0.027,0.529)\n RGB{N0f8}(0.0,0.302,1.0)\n RGB{N0f8}(0.0,0.502,0.149)\n RGB{N0f8}(1.0,0.929,0.0)\n RGB{N0f8}(1.0,0.549,0.0)\n RGB{N0f8}(0.894,0.012,0.012)\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"constant"}]
